tribution to gender and media studies, and help to illuminate the complexity of our current moment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism and mass mediazUnited States. 0aFeminism and mass media-United States. 0aFeminism and mass media. 0aMass media and womenzUnited States. 0aMass media and women-United States. 0aSexism in mass media. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aGender and Sexuality : Feminist. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aTripodi, Francesca, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848197540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438481975423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438481975/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles